Senior Special Assistant to the President on National Assembly Matters (Senate), Senator Babajide Omoworare has said President Muhammadu Buhari did not undermine the office of  Vice President Yemi Osinbajo, by travelling without transmitting a  letter that would allow him to act,  to the National Assembly.  Sen. Omoworare alongside his colleague Hon. Umar Yakub, who made the clarification today while briefing journalists in Abuja also debunked reports of misunderstanding between the Office of the President and that of the Vice President. He noted that the constitution permits the President to work from anywhere in the world.  Our Correspondent, Raliat Adenekan reports that there have been mixed reactions trailing the signing of the Amended Deep Offshore and Inland basin production sharing contract bill by President Muhammadu Buhari who is currently on a private visit in London.